Paulson Resorts Win Approval for $30 Million Bankruptcy Loan

-- B y   D a v i d   M c L a u g h l i n
-- 
2011-04-13T19:39:07Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-13/paulson-resorts-win-approval-for-30-million-bankruptcy-loan-1-.html
A group of resorts owned by hedge
fund Paulson & Co. and other investors won court approval to
borrow a $30 million loan while in bankruptcy.  U.S. Bankruptcy Judge Sean Lane in  New York  gave final
approval to the loan at a court hearing today. Paulson and Five
Mile Capital Partners have agreed to provide the financing,
according to court papers.  The five resorts, including the Grand Wailea resort in
Maui, Hawaii, filed for bankruptcy in February. Paulson and
other investors took ownership of the properties and three other
resorts through a foreclosure, according to a statement from the
ownership group.  The case is In re MSR Resort Golf Course LLC, 11-10372,
 U.S. Bankruptcy Court , Southern District of New York
( Manhattan ).  To contact the reporter on this story:
David McLaughlin in New York at 
 dmclaughlin9@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
John Pickering at   jpickering@bloomberg.net . 